## Phase-Level Access

Within the execute-plan skill, individual phases can override the command-level `full-access` profile using the `**Access**` field in the plan:

| Phase Access | Tool Access | When Used |
|-------------|-------------|-----------|
| `full-access` | All tools (default) | Implementation phases — types, backend, frontend, tests |
| `read-only` | Read, Grep, Glob only; output to `flow/` dirs | Review, audit, analysis, documentation-only phases |

**Rules**:
- If a phase has no `**Access**` field, it defaults to `full-access` (backward compatible)
- Phase access is enforced for the duration of that phase only — the next phase reverts to its own access level
- High-complexity phases (7+) get an automatic read-only verification check after implementation (scope drift detection)
- The create-plan skill auto-assigns access levels based on phase name and scope

See `rules/patterns/plans-templates.mdc` for the phase template with the `Access` field.

---

## Enforcement

Profiles are enforced by convention — the `AGENT_PROFILE` header in each command file and the `## Tool Access` section in each skill file reference this document. The LLM must respect the boundaries defined here.

**If a skill needs to perform an action outside its profile**:
1. Stop and explain why the action is needed
2. Ask the user for explicit permission
3. Document the exception in the review output
